on":"","dateOfDiscovery":"","placeOfDiscovery":"","provenance":"","historicalContext":[],"objectHistory":"Lunette plac\u00e9e au-dessus de la partie centrale (repr\u00e9sentant une Ascension) d\u0027un polyptyque compos\u00e9 de quinze panneaux, ex\u00e9cut\u00e9 entre 1495 et 1498 pour le ma\u00eetre-autel de la basilique des B\u00e9n\u00e9dictins de San Pietro \u00e0 P\u00e9rouse.\r\nCe polyptyque fut saisi en 1797 par les arm\u00e9es fran\u00e7aises, emport\u00e9 en France, et ses \u00e9l\u00e9ments dispers\u00e9s dans diff\u00e9rents mus\u00e9es et \u00e9glises.\r\nLa lunette a \u00e9t\u00e9 d\u00e9pos\u00e9e dans l\u0027\u00e9glise Saint-Gervais-Saint-Protais \u00e0 Paris sous le Premier Empire, puis au mus\u00e9e de Lyon en 1952, afin de couronner \u00e0 nouveau la partie centrale du polyptyque, l\u0027Ascension du Christ (envoy\u00e9e au mus\u00e9e de Lyon en 1811).","jabachInventory":"","napoleonInventory":"","previousOwner":[],"acquisitionDetails":[{"mode":"conqu\u00eate militaire","doubt":"","dates":[{"type":"date","value":"1797","startYear":1797,"endYear":1797}]}],"ownedBy":"Etat","heldBy":"Mus\u00e9e du Louvre, D\u00e9partement des Peintures","longTermLoanTo":"Mus\u00e9e des Beaux-Arts, Lyon","index":{"Mode d\u0027acquisition":[{"value":"conqu\u00eate militaire"}]},"bibliography":[{"bibliographyRef":"Emiliani, Andrea ; Laclotte, Michel (dir.), Opere d\u0027arte prese in Italia : nel corso della Campagna napoleonica 1796-1814 e riprese da Antonio Canova nel 1815, Bologne \/ Faenza, 2018","bibliographyDate":"2018","bibliographyDetail":"p. 218, n\u00b0215","comparison":false}],"exhibition":[],"relatedWork":[{"objectUrl":"https:\/\/collections.louvre.fr\/ark:\/53355\/cl010058727","type":"Polyptyque"},{"objectUrl":"https:\/\/collections.louvre.fr\/ark:\/53355\/cl010058728","type":"Polyptyque"},{"objectUrl":"https:\/\/collections.louvre.fr\/ark:\/53355\/cl010058889","type":"Polyptyque"}],"image":[{"urlImage":"https:\/\/collections.louvre.fr\/media\/cache\/larg